        "created_at": "2022-09-15T23:54:24.549Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I am trying to compile with FIPS aware openssl on RHEL 8.  The one static openssl library I found is old and gives me linking error in the crypto library.  It is based on 1.1.1c which is two years old.  I can\u2019t use an updated version like 1.1.1k/m from <a href=\"http://openssl.org\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">openssl.org</a> due to FIPS compliance issue.  So, that\u2019s why I am thinking about linking dynamically.  In my env., I will always have openssl installed so the runtime .so should always be there.<br>\nCould you point me out how to change the openssl part from static to dynamic?  Is it just a change to the CMake configure to turn that static linking off?  I am compiling on a RHEL 8 host, not using the docker build env.<br>\nThanks</p>",
